R Notebook

Growth chamber well water experimen. Peanut were inoculated with five different fungal isolates from Alabama cotton fields (Mortierellas and Linnemannia) and from the Old Rotation (P. citrinum)

here we analyze and visualize the growth chamber results (Phi2, shoot and root biomass)

We decided to exclude treatment NVP5.

photosynq_sub <-  photosynq %>%
  subset(!Treatment %in% c("NVP5"))

Lets first analyze and visualize the shoot biomass data We used the linear model to test the effect of the treatments (fungal inoculations) in the shoot dry biomass of the peanuts. With this we tested one-way ANOVA to test the differences of means of the treatments and we lsmeeans we got the p-value btw treatments

lm.shoot <- lm(Shootbiomass~ Treatment, data = photosynq_sub)
#plot(lm.shoot)
summary(lm.shoot)
anova(lm.shoot)
lsmeans.shoot <- emmeans(lm.shoot, ~ Treatment, adjust = "tukey") # estimate lsmeans

Results_lsmeeans <- cld(object = lsmeans.shoot,
                        Letters = letters, reversed = TRUE, details = TRUE) # contrast with Tukey ajustment

Now lets look at the Phi2. Phi2 measures the amount of incoming light that the plant uses for photosynthesis. Here we analyzed the light used for photosynthesis (Phi2) against the days post drought since these measurements were taken throughout the experiment. For the visualization we selected only a few time points

lm.phi2 <- lm(Phi2~ Treatment*as.factor(dayspostdrought), data = photosynq_sub)
#plot(lm.)
summary(lm.phi2)
